Introducing: Reggie Ray Small💙

Born 7/23/23
7lbs 14 oz and 21in long
9:00pm on the dot with Taylor Swift playing in the OR✨

We are so in love with our sweet baby boy!🥹

Saturday night I was having really bad back pain from my arthritis flaring up + pregnancy pains… So Sunday afternoon we were advised to go to the hospital for L&D. They were going to make sure I wasn’t in labor, but mainly just going to give me some pain meds so I’d be able to survive the following two days until the scheduled version/possible c-section (since baby was breech).

They first gave me a single dose of Percocet and almost sent me on my way… but then the doctor said he actually didn’t want me to leave with my level of uncontrolled pain. (Since it was Sunday and Monday was a “holiday” in Utah for Pioneer Day, there wasn’t much medical help available other than the ER). 

Soooo they offered to do the C section that night! My amniotic fluid was too low for the doctor to attempt the version. We already had our hospital bags packed in the car, and we were just too excited to meet baby boy, that we decided to go for the c-section that night! (I was also very done with all the pain and just wanted baby OUT to get my arthritis flare up to chill out.) 

We went in for the c section at 8:50pm and baby was out at 9pm! I requested for Taylor Swift to play in the OR, and it was probably the best decision I’ve ever made.😉🤪 The pain meds must have been really working, because the nurse told me she’ll never listen to Love Story without thinking of me singing along while on the operating table haha!

The doctor held up Reggie and I got to see him, but not hold him, because they had to take him to the NICU for the first 1.5hr of his life. Luckily, Jackson got to be with him every second! I finished getting sewn up and was taken to our mom/baby recovery room and had Jackson FaceTime me so I could at least see Reggie! We FaceTimed our families to share the moment with them too. It made what could have been a sad, lonely moment for me, into a joyous and exciting time still! 

Finally baby was brought back in and I got to hold him and cuddle skin to skin for the first time! 

He’s healthy and happy and such a sweet boy with the cutest little coos. C-section recovery is going well, and cuddling the most perfect baby boy makes it all worth it!!!

The happiest moment😭❤️ He was only in the NICU for two hours, but let me just say it was the longest two hours of my life🥺
